body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/457\n\n## Problem (never-block violation)\n`pm health` can hang during the vectorization check with NO output until killed by an external timeout; same tracker returns immediately when vectorization is skipped. Reproduces with extensions disabled. Health is an agent-loop gating command — it must never hang silently.\n\n## Proposed fix\nHard timeout + progress/heartbeat around the vectorization probe (bounded like the lock-wait work in 010bb349); on timeout, report vectorization check as timed-out with skip hint (--skip-vectors) instead of hanging; investigate the underlying blocking call (likely embedding provider probe without socket timeout — same family as the GH-455 item).\n\n## Definition of done\npm health always returns within a bounded time with partial results on vectorization stall; timeout covered by spec with a hanging fake provider; docs note --skip-vectors."
